						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Chōḻa, Parāntaka I, Year 39 = 946 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Register an endowment of 140 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold by Kāchchuvan Kēchuvaṉ of Tiruveḷḷaṟai, for feeding two Brāhmaṇas versed in the Vēdas. The temple is called Tiruvanaikkallil-Bhaṭārakar at Tiruveḷḷaṟai. The <hi rend="italic">mūlapariḍai</hi> of the village undertook to supervise the endowment. </p>						

